pha|\"Fuckyounoah\" peaked at number 37 on the NZ Hot Singles Chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4772|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|date=November 11, 2019|accessdate=November 9, 2019}}</ref>}} || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"This Is Us\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(with [[Jimmie Allen]])</span><ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/this-is-us-single/1497381776|title=This Is Us \u2013 Single by Jimmie Allen & Noah Cyrus|website=Apple Music|accessdate=February 22, 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2020\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"I Got So High That I Saw Jesus\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/au/album/i-got-so-high-that-i-saw-jesus-single/1501869110|title=I Got So High That I Saw Jesus \u2013 Single by Noah Cyrus|website=Apple Music|accessdate=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014{{efn|group=upper-alpha|\"I Got So High That I Saw Jesus\" peaked at number 33 on the NZ Hot Singles Chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4838|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>}} || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n|-\n| colspan=\"18\" style=\"font-size:85%\"| \"\u2014\" denotes release that did not chart or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n==== As featured artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"9\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| Certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-s