b|author=Steffen Hung |url=http://www.swisscharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Alan+Walker+feat.+Noah+Cyrus+%26+Digital+Farm+Animals&titel=All+Falls+Down&cat=s |title=Alan Walker feat. Noah Cyrus & Digital Farm Animals \u2013 All Falls Down |website=Swisscharts.com|date= |accessdate=2017-11-17}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Dance/Electronic Songs|US<br>Dance]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/music/noah-cyrus/chart-history/dance-electronic-songs|title=Noah Cyrus Chart History: Dance/Electronic Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Chasing Colors]]\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">([[Marshmello]] and [[Ookay]] featuring Noah Cyrus)</span>\n| rowspan=\"4\"| 2017\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 31\n|\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Waiting\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">([[Jake Bugg]] featuring Noah Cyrus)</span>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| ''[[Hearts That Strain]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[All Falls Down (Alan Walker song)|All Falls Down]]\"<br/><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">([[Alan Walker (music producer)|Alan Walker]] featuring Noah Cyrus and [[Digital Farm Animals]])</span>\n| 95 || 29 || 17 || 75 || 6 || 1 || 4<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sverigetopplistan.se/|title=Sverigetopplistan \u2013 Sveriges Officiella Topplista|publisher=[[Sverigetopplistan]]|accessdate=January 13, 2018}}</ref> || 29 || 11\n|\n* ARIA: Gold<ref name=\"ariasingles2017\" />\n* GLF: Platinum<ref name=\"GLF\"/>\n* MC: Gold<ref name=\"MC\"/>\n*RIAA: Gold<ref name=\"RIAA\" />\n| ''[[Different World (Alan Walker album)|Different World]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Slow (Matoma song)|Slow]]\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">([[Matoma]] featuring Noah Cyrus)</span>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 30<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vglista.no/topplister/topp-20-single-2017-47/|title=VG-lista \u2013 Topp 20 Single uke 47, 2017|publisher=[[VG-lista]]|accessdate=November 25, 2017}}</ref> || 87 || \u2014 || 31\n|\n| ''[[One in a Million (Matoma album)|One In a Million]]''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Expensive\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(Rence featuring Noah Cyrus)</span>\n| rowspan=\"1\"| 2019\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014\n|\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"13\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:8pt;\"| \"\u2014\" denotes items which were not released in that country or failed to chart.\n|}\n\n====Promotional singles====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of promotional singles\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Almost Famous\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[It's Beginning to Look a Lot Like Christmas]]\"\n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Other artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n!Notes\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Tulsa Time\" (Rokman Remix)\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2017\n| [[Billy Ray Cyrus]], Derek Jones\n| ''[[Set the Record Straight (Billy Ray Cyrus album)|Set the Record Straight]]''\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Christmas (Baby Please Come Home)]]\"<br/><small>([[Amazon Music|Amazon]] exclusive)</small>\n| {{n/a}}\n| {{n/a|Non-album song}}\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Come On My Way\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|Holdan\n|''I Lost My Friends In The Spring''\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Ecstasy\"\n|[[XXXTentacion]]\n|''[[Bad Vibes Forever]]''\n|\n|}\n\n===Songwriting credits===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:20em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Artist(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Album\n!Notes\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Flashbacks\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2019\n|[[Chris Brown]]\n|''[[Indigo (Chris Brown album)|Indigo]]''\n|Co-writer\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"The Girls\"\n|[[Iggy Azalea]], [[Pabllo Vittar]]\n|''[[Wicked Lips]]''\n|Co-writer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Work\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |2017\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Radio Disney Music Awards]]\n|Best Breakup Song\n|\"[[Make Me (Cry)]]\"\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Best New Artist\n| rowspan=\"3\" |Herself\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Europe Music Award|MTV Europe Music Awards]]\n|Best Push\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|PETA's Annual Libby Award\n|Best Peta2 Ad\n|Speaking up against [[SeaWorld]]\n|{{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n||[[WDM Radio Awards]]<ref>{{cite web|title=WDM Radio Awards|url=http://los40.com.mx/especiales/wdm-Radio-Awards/nominados.html|accessdate=20 February 2018}}</ref>\n| Best Bass Track\n|\"[[All Falls Down (Alan Walker song)|All Falls Down]]\"\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards|Nichelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]\n|Favorite Breakout Artist\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Herself\n|{{Nom}}\n|-\n|[[MTV Video Music Award|MTV Video Music Awards]]\n|Push Artist Of The Year\n|{{Nom}}\n|}\n\n==Tours==\n===Headlining===\n* The Good Cry Tour (2018)\n*The Not So Tour, Tour (2020)\n\n===Opening act===\n* [[Katy Perry]] \u2013 [[Witness: The Tour]] (2017)\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{notelist-ua}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb name|1682324}}\n* {{AllMusic|id=mn0002817246}}\n* {{Twitter}} <!-- followed by verified acct of sister https://twitter.com/MileyCyrus/following -->\n\n{{Noah Cyrus}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cyrus, Noah}}\n[[Category:2000 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:Cyrus family|Noah]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Nashville, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:Syco Music artists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:Singers from Nashville, Tennessee]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American singer and actress}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Noah Cyrus\n| image              = Noah Cyrus VMA 2018.jpg\n| caption            = Cyrus at the [[2018 MTV Video Music Awards]]\n| birth_name         = Noah Lindsey Cyrus<ref name=\"Parade\">{{cite web|url=https://parade.com/22254/linzlowe/billy-ray-cyrus-tish-cyrus-announce-divorce/|title=Billy Ray Cyrus, Tish Cyrus Announce Divorce|last=Lowe|first=Lindsay|website=[[Parade (magazine)|Parade]]|date=June 14, 2013|accessdate=February 17, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"ISWC\">{{cite web|url=http://iswcnet.cisac.org/MWI/result/list.do?pageNumber=1&localEngineCode=999|title=Your query : Creator's Name begins with CYRUS NOAH on any territories (Domestic works)|website=[[International Standard Musical Work Code|ISWC]]|access-date=February 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|2000|1|8|mf=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Nashville, Tennessee]], U.S.\n| occupation         = {{flatlist|\n* Singer\n* songwriter\n* actress\n}}\n| years active       = 2002\u2013present\n| parents            = {{plainlist|\n* [[Billy Ray Cyrus]] (father)\n* [[Tish Cyrus]] (mother)\n}}\n| relatives          = {{plainlist|\n* [[Ron Cyrus]] (grandfather)\n* [[Trace Cyrus]] (brother)\n* [[Miley Cyrus]] (sister)\n* [[Brandi Cyrus]] (sister)\n}}\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background         = solo_singer\n| genre              = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Electro (music)|electro]]\n}}\n| instrument         = Vocals\n| label              = {{flatlist|\n* RECORDS\n* [[Syco Music|Syco]]\n* [[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n}}\n| associated_acts = <!-- only musical acts significant and notable to this musical artist's career - see infobox instructions -->\n}}\n}}\n'''Noah Lindsey Cyrus'''<ref name=\"Parade\"/><ref name=\"ISWC\"/> (born January 8, 2000)<ref name=allmusicbio>{{cite web|url= https://www.allmusic.com/artist/noah-cyrus-mn0002817246/biography|title=Noah Cyrus Biography|first=Heather|last=Phares|publisher=[[AllMusic.com]]|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref> is an American singer, songwriter, and actress. In 2016, she released her debut single \"[[Make Me (Cry)]]\", featuring vocals from [[Labrinth]].\n\nCyrus is the fifth child of [[Billy Ray Cyrus|Billy Ray]] and [[Tish Cyrus]], and she is the youngest sibling of [[Trace Cyrus|Trace]], [[Brandi Cyrus|Brandi]], and [[Miley Cyrus]]. She was named one of [[Time (magazine)|''Time'']]'s 30 Most Influential Teens in 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/5003930/most-influential-teens-2017|title=The 30 Most Influential Teens of 2017|accessdate=November 4, 2017|date=November 3, 2017|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nCyrus was born January 8, 2000, in [[Nashville, Tennessee]], to producer and director [[Tish Cyrus]] and country singer [[Billy Ray Cyrus]]. Her parents have had a volatile marriage, each filing for divorce on different occasions, but restoring their relationship. Her siblings include [[Miley Cyrus|Miley]], Braison, [[Brandi Cyrus|Brandi]], [[Trace Cyrus|Trace]], and Christopher Cyrus, who have also mostly become musicians and entertainers.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.editorchoice.com/cyrus-family/2/|title=Revealing Facts About The Cyrus Family|date=2019-08-18|website=Editor Choice|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref> Their paternal grandfather, [[Ron Cyrus]], was a politician in Kentucky.\n\n==Acting career==\nAt the age of two, Cyrus began her acting career, playing Gracie Hebert on the sixth episode of the television show ''[[Doc (2001 TV series)|Doc]]''. She was a background dancer in the 2009 film ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'', and played small roles in six episodes of the [[Disney Channel Original Series]] ''[[Hannah Montana]]''. She appeared in the [[Direct-to-video|straight-to-DVD]] movie ''[[Mostly Ghostly (film)|Mostly Ghostly]]'', where she was spotted as a Trick or Treater.<ref>[http://www.juniorcelebs.com/noah-cyrus-in-mostly-ghostly/ Noah Cyrus in Mostly Ghostly] at JuniorCelebs.com</ref> In 2008, her first movie role was in the English version of the anime feature film ''[[Ponyo]]'', in which she voiced the title character. She sang the English version of the theme song to that film, performing alongside [[Frankie Jonas]]. Between 2009 and 2010, Cyrus ran a webshow with [[Emily Grace Reaves]], called ''The Noie and Ems Show''.<ref>{{cite news |first=John |last=Young |title=Hayao Miyazaki's 'Ponyo' gets U.S. release date |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=March 24, 2009 |accessdate=March 24, 2009 |quote=English voice cast that includes ... Noah Cyrus |url=http://news-briefs.ew.com/2009/03/miyazaki-ponyo.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090328115332/http://news-briefs.ew.com/2009/03/miyazaki-ponyo.html |archive-date=March 28, 2009 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first=Jocelyn |last=Vena |title=Cyrus And Jonas Siblings Team Up For Miyazaki Movie |work=[[MTV]] Movies Blog |date=April 3, 2009 |accessdate=April 4, 2009 |quote=voice actors in the animated flick, \"Ponyo,\" by \"Sed Away\" director Hayao Miyazaki. |url=http://moviesblog.mtv.com/2009/04/03/cyrus-and-jonas-siblings-team-up-for-miyazaki-movie/}}</ref>\n\n==Singing career==\nOn November 15, 2016, it was announced that Cyrus had inked a record deal with [[Barry Weiss]]' record label, called RECORDS, and later signed a management deal with [[Maverick (company)|Maverick]] under [[Adam Leber]]. She released her debut single \"[[Make Me (Cry)]]\" featuring [[Labrinth]] that same day.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Drysdale|first1=Jennifer|title=Noah Cyrus Releases Debut Single 'Make Me (Cry)' -- Listen!|url=http://www.etonline.com/music/202904_noah_cyrus_releases_debut_single_make_me_cry_listen/|website=Entertainment Tonight|accessdate=3 August 2017|language=en}}</ref> In December 2016, she released an acoustic performance of \"Almost Famous\". She also provided vocals on the song \"[[Chasing Colors]]\" performed by [[Marshmello]] and [[Ookay]], which was released in February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Wass|first1=Mike|title=Noah Cyrus Dabbles In Dance On \"Chasing Colors\" {{!}} Idolator|url=http://www.idolator.com/7658078/noah-cyrus-chasing-colors-marshmello-ookay-full-song|website=Music News, Reviews, and Gossip on Idolator.com|accessdate=26 April 2017|date=24 February 2017}}</ref> On April 14, 2017, she released another single, called \"[[Stay Together (Noah Cyrus song)|Stay Together]]\",<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stutz|first1=Colin|title=Noah Cyrus Finds Love at a Party With New Song 'Stay Together'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/7760460/noah-cyrus-stay-together-new-song-stream|website=Billboard|accessdate=3 August 2017}}</ref> followed by the single \"I'm Stuck\", released on May 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Spanos|first1=Brittany|title=Hear Noah Cyrus' Country-Pop New Song 'I'm Stuck'|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/hear-noah-cyrus-country-pop-new-single-im-stuck-w484379|website=Rolling Stone|accessdate=3 August 2017}}</ref> On September 21, 2017, she released another single \"[[Again (Noah Cyrus song)|Again]]\" featuring [[XXXTentacion]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Again (feat. XXXTENTACION) - Single by Noah Cyrus on Apple Music|date=2017-09-22|url=https://itunes.apple.com/album/again-feat-xxxtentacion-single/id1286870860|language=en-us|accessdate=2017-09-22}}</ref> From September 19, 2017, to November 1, 2017, she opened for [[Katy Perry]] on the [[Witness: The Tour]]. In November 2017, Cyrus made an appearance at Emo Nite in Los Angeles for a surprise DJ set which included some of her and her brother Trace Cyrus' music.<ref>{{cite news |last1=LaCroix |first1=Jane |title=Noah & Trace Cyrus Teamed Up To DJ A Secret Emo Nite Event In LA & Miley Would Be Proud |url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2017/11/09/noah-cyrus-trace-cyrus-dj-emo-nite-event-los-angeles-video/ |accessdate=June 18, 2018 |work=Hollywood Life |agency=SheKnows Media |publisher=Penske Business Media |date=November 10, 2017}}</ref> \"My Way\", a collaboration with electronic group One Bit, was released on November 24, 2017.\n\nHer first single of 2018, \"We Are...\" featuring Danish artist [[M\u00d8]], was released on February 7. Cyrus released \"Team\", a collaboration with [[Max Schneider|MAX]], on May 11, 2018. A follow up collaboration \"Lately\", was released on June 15, 2018, with Tanner Alexander. On July 9, 2018, Cyrus announced her first headlining tour, The Good Cry Tour.<ref>{{cite news|last=Spanos|first=Brittany|title=Noah Cyrus Announces First Headlining Tour|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/noah-cyrus-announces-first-headlining-tour-697671/|work=Rolling Stone|date=July 9, 2018|accessdate=July 10, 2018}}</ref> \"Live or Die\", a collaboration with [[Lil Xan]], was released on August 20, 2018. Norwegian DJ [[Matoma]] featured Cyrus on \"[[Slow (Matoma song)|Slow]]\" in 2017, which was featured on his second album ''[[One in a Million (Matoma album)|One in a Million]]'', released on August 24, 2018. Cyrus released her new EP, ''[[Good Cry]]'', on September 21, 2018, featuring new songs including \"Mad at You\" a collaboration with [[Gallant (singer)|Gallant]] and \"Punches\" a collaboration with [[LP (singer)|LP]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Close|first=Paris|title=Noah Cyrus Says New EP Addresses Her Struggles With Anxiety, Depression|url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2018-08-23-noah-cyrus-says-new-ep-addresses-her-struggles-with-anxiety-depression/|date=August 24, 2018|accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref> DJ [[Alan Walker (DJ)|Alan Walker]] featured Cyrus' vocals on \"[[All Falls Down (Alan Walker song)|All Falls Down]]\" from his debut studio album, ''[[Different World (Alan Walker album)|Different World]]'', which was released on December 14, 2018. On July 31, 2019, Cyrus released a song called \"[[July (Noah Cyrus song)|July]]\", as the first single of her upcoming debut album.<ref>{{cite|url=https://www.idolator.com/7842590/noah-cyrus-returns-with-a-new-single-called-july|title=Noah Cyrus Returns With A New Single Called \"July\"|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=July 31, 2019|accessdate=July 31, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nCyrus dated rapper [[Lil Xan]] from June to September 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/music/noah-cyrus-lil-xan-dating|title=Noah Cyrus Is Dating Soundcloud Rapper Lil Xan: 'It's New,' Says Source|website=people.com|date=July 31, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/noah-cyrus-and-lil-xan-split-accuse-each-other-of-cheating/amp|title=Noah Cyrus and Lil Xan Split After a Month of Dating, Accuse Each Other of Cheating|website=usmagazine|date=September 4, 2018}}</ref> Cyrus is known to be vocal about her [[mental health]] challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://missoulian.com/people/noah-cyrus-reveals-pains-of-being-child-star/article_190ee1c7-5c80-5992-8f03-db22aeb182f5.html|title=Noah Cyrus reveals pains of being child star|first=By|last=Celebretainment|website=missoulian.com}}</ref> She experiences [[Depression disorder|depression]] and [[anxiety]], with [[panic attack]]s as part of the latter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/noah-cyrus-depression-anxiety|title=Noah Cyrus Discussed Her Experiences With Depression and Anxiety|first=Emily|last=Wang|website=Teen Vogue}}</ref> She has stated she goes to therapy to address these challenges.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nz.news.yahoo.com/noah-cyrus-reveals-pains-being-080446126.html|title=Noah Cyrus reveals pains of being child star|website=nz.news.yahoo.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tucson.com/people/noah-cyrus-reveals-pains-of-being-child-star/article_e2ee2d64-4c38-5ae1-93c9-ad21d61db7e8.html|title=Noah Cyrus reveals pains of being child star|first=By|last=Celebretainment|website=Arizona Daily Star}}</ref> Her music often relates to her struggles, such as in her EP ''[[Good Cry (EP)|Good Cry]]'' with \"Sadness\" and \"Topanga\" and somber songs such as \"July\" and \"Lonely\".\n\n==Philanthropy==\nIn 2013, Cyrus used her 13th birthday as an opportunity to raise funds for the ban of using [[horse-drawn vehicle|horse-drawn carriages]] in [[New York City]].<ref>Erin Durkin,\"[http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/noah-cyrus-jumps-central-park-carriage-horse-ban-article-1.1236067#ixzz2HUIKsHBG Miley Cyrus' Younger Sister Noah Jumps into Campaign to Ban Central Park Carriage Horses],\" ''New York Daily News'', January 8, 2013.</ref> More recently, she has worked with [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals|PETA]]. First appearing in an ad protesting the use of animal dissection in high school science classes instead of plastic ones or virtual dissection programs. Then in another supporting a [[SeaWorld]] boycott.<ref>Zack Seemayer, \"[http://www.etonline.com/news/162474_noah_cyrus_stars_gruesome_peta_ad_against_animal_dissection/ Noah Cyrus Stars in Gruesome PETA Ad Against Animal Dissection],\" ET,  April 8, 2015.</ref><ref>Ashley Iasimone, \"Noah Cyrus Submerges Herself in a Water Tank for PETA Campaign Against SeaWorld ,\" ''[http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8013950/noah-cyrus-peta-seaworld-orcas-campaign Billboard]'', 24 October 2017.</ref> In 2019, after the releasing of her single ''Lonely'', Noah teamed up with the Crystal Campaign and released a merchandising collection called The Lonely Collection which funds were collected to [[The Jed Foundation]], a non-profit organisation in the USA that exists to protect emotional health and prevent [[suicide]] for our nation's teens and young adults. Later, Cyrus joined the [[mobile app]] [[Depop]] and put on sale her own old clothes and its funds were also donated to The Jed Foundation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.flaunt.com/content/noah-cyrus-the-crystal-campaign|title=Noah Cyrus {{!}} The Crystal Campaign|website=Flaunt Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-13}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| rowspan=4|2008\n| ''[[Hannah Montana and Miley Cyrus: Best of Both Worlds Concert]]''\n| Herself\n| Musical film\n|-\n| ''[[Mostly Ghostly (film)|Mostly Ghostly]]''\n| Trick or Treater\n| Cameo\n|-\n| ''[[Ponyo]]''\n| Ponyo\n| Voice role (English version)\n|-\n| ''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]''\n| Little Dancing Girl\n| Cameo\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Television roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2002\u201304\n| ''[[Doc (2001 TV series)|Doc]]''\n| Gracie Herbert\n| 9 episodes <br> Recurring role (Seasons 2\u20135)\n|-\n| 2006\u201310\n| ''[[Hannah Montana]]''\n| Various roles\n| 6 episodes <br> Recurring role (Seasons 1\u20132, 4)\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''[[The Emperor's New School]]''\n| Voice \n| Episode: \"Guaka Rules\"\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2012\n|''The Joey & Elise Show''\n| Herself\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| ''The Hugo & Rita Show''\n| Hugo and Rita\n| 4 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''Take 2''\n| Deb / Adamley / Allison\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Carpool Karaoke: The Series]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Cyrus Family\"\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Other roles\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present\n| ''Stoney Stories''\n| Herself (Voice)\n| YouTube Series<ref>{{Cite news|title=Noah Cyrus - Stoney Stories|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pbrytoL-Z9k|date=8 August 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2019\n| ''[[I Think I'm Okay|I Think I'm OKAY]]''\n| Herself\n| Music video by [[Machine Gun Kelly (rapper)|Machine Gun Kelly]]<ref>{{Cite new|title=Machine Gun Kelly, YUNGBLUD, Travis Barker - I Think I'm OKAY [Official Music Video]|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wK-8TCDrbV8|date=13 June 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|''[[Graduation (Benny Blanco and Juice Wrld song)|Graduation]]''\n|Becky\n|Music video by [[Benny Blanco|benny blanco]] & [[Juice Wrld|Juice WRLD]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ As director\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Again (Noah Cyrus song)|Again]]''\n| rowspan=2|Herself\n| Her own music video\n|-\n|2019\n|''Lonely''\n|Her own music video co-directed with Symone Ridgell\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8em;\" | Title\n! rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\" | Details\n!Peak<br>chart<br> positions\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"|[[Heatseekers Album|US]]<br>[[Heatseekers Album|Heat]]<br><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=ts_chart_artistname:Noah%20Cyrus&f%5B1%5D=ss_chart_search_title:*Good%20Cry*&f%5B2%5D=itm_field_chart_id:Heatseekers%20Albums&f%5B3%5D=ss_bb_type:chart_item&type=1&artist=Noah%20Cyrus&title=Good%20Cry|title=Chart Search {{!}} Billboard|website=www.billboard.com|language=en|access-date=2018-10-04}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''[[Good Cry]]''\n|\n* Released: September 21, 2018\n* Label: RECORDS/[[Columbia Records|Columbia]]\n* Formats: [[CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]], [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n|13\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |''The End Of Everything''\n|\n* Released: May 15, 2020\n* Label: RECORDS/Columbia\n* Formats: CD, Digital download, streaming\n| \u2014\n|}\n\